2.10	Raymond_Kappe	Ray Kappe	Ray Kappe (born 1927 in Minneapolis to Romanian immigrant parents) is an award winning architect and educator in Southern California. In 1972, he resigned his position as Founding Chair of the Department of Architecture at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona and along with a group of faculty and students, started what eventually came to be known as the Southern California Institute of Architecture (SCI-Arc).	
